{"key":"processedPost-10412460","value":{"id":10412460,"first":10412112,"last":10412533,"when":1243521922,"utime":"05/28/09 05:45 PM","content":"If you stand a cylinder on end, the water will drain by gravity to the other end and the top will dry out.&nbsp; That's why I found you get much better performance from straw logs when they're laying down.<br /><br />Also, there's no law that says a rectangle substrate can only fruit from one of its six sides.&nbsp; You can easily pop them out of the pan and stand on edge.&nbsp; A few growers have done this and had pretty amazing results.&nbsp; Moisture control becomes labor intensive, but if you're experimenting, go for it.<br />RR","title":"Re: Cylinder?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}